I"<<p>Adolescence exhibits <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/migration-lineage-correlates-with-novelty-seeking-genes">novelty-seeking</a> and <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/contrastive-learning-is-deviant-based-norm-setting">norm avoidance</a>. This might be an <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/predestined-learning-breaks-nature-nurture-dichotomy">innate</a> mechanism for <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/psychological-foraging-resembles-simulated-annealing">effective search</a> in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/internalizing-beliefs-incurs-ideological-debt">ideology space</a>. In this view, adolescence is an exploratory phase of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/psychological-foraging-resembles-simulated-annealing">cognitive-behavioral foraging</a>.</p>
